Sentencas: A challenging task in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is seeking for an alternative electrolyte, enabling high ionic conduction at relatively low operating temperatures, i.e., 300-600 degree celsius.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Proton-conducting candidates, in particular, hold a significant promise due to their low transport activation energy to deliver protons.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Here, a unique hierarchical TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 structure is developed inside an intercalated TiO2-SrTiO3 core as yolk decorating densely packed flake TiO2 as shell, creating plentiful nano-heterointerfaces with a continuous TiO2 and SrTiO3 in-house interfaces, as well the interfaces between TiO2-SrTiO3 yolk and TiO2 shell.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It exhibits a reduced activation energy, down to 0.225 eV, and an unexpectedly high proton conductivity at low temperature, e.g., 0.084 S cm(-1) at 550 degree celsius, confirmed by experimentally H/D isotope method and proton-filtrating membrane measurement.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Raman mapping technique identifies the presence of hydrogenated HO-Sr bonds, providing further evidence for proton conduction.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: And its interfacial conduction is comparatively analyzed with a directly-mixing TiO2-SrTiO3 composite electrolyte.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Consequently, a single fuel cell based on the TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 heterogeneous electrolyte delivers a good peak power density of 799.7 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C. These findings highlight a dexterous nano-heterointerface design strategy of highly proton-conductive electrolytes at reduced operating temperatures for SOFC technology.
Titulo: Enriching Nano-Heterointerfaces in Proton Conducting TiO2-SrTiO3@TiO2 Yolk-Shell Electrolyte for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
